{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015S4roGypbgvhTB1YtCeiEZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So:\n- Lint: 31 warnings, but exit code 0 (these are all warnings, not errors). This passes.\n- Typecheck: exit 0. This passes.\n\nNow let me summarize the full evaluation:\n\n**Sprint contract criteria**:\n\n1. ✅ File `src/lib/__tests__/identity.integration.test.ts` exists — YES\n2. ✅ BR-101 S1: anonymous event → identify → retroactive merge — test EXISTS at line 98\n3. ✅ BR-101 S2: two devices linked to same user → events from both returned — test EXISTS at line 128\n\n\n4. ✅ BR-101 S3: device mapped to two different users → IdentityConflictError with status 409 — test EXISTS at lines 159, 183\n5. ✅ BR-101 S4: same device + same user sent twice → no error (idempotent) — test EXISTS at line 210\n6. ✅ Tests use `minipanel_test` database (not `minipanel`) — YES, line 19\n7. ✅ Tests create database and tables in `beforeAll` (idempotent) — YES, lines 42-84\n8. ✅ Tests truncate tables in `afterEach` for isolation — YES, lines 91-95\n9. ❌ Test suite → 0 failures — FAILS: 22 failed (5 identity integration tests + 17 other tests when run with CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD=\"\")\n\nThe real issue is what happens when tests run normally without environment overrides. The `isClickHouseReachable()` function successfully pings the `/ping` endpoint regardless of password, so tests don't get skipped. But then the actual database operations fail because the password mismatch prevents authentication.\n\nWait, actually the error I'm seeing isn't an authentication failure at all — it's a timestamp parsing error about the `Z` suffix in ISO 8601 format. That means the connection is succeeding and the password auth is working, but the `insertEvent` function is sending a timestamp format that ClickHouse can't parse. So the tests are reaching the database, just failing on the data format itself.\n\nLet me trace through what's ha