nd 5/10 since the sprint's core objective—demonstrating that tests pass against a real ClickHouse instance—isn't achieved, even though the test file is structurally complete and correct.\n\nNow I need to write up the evaluation. But first, let me clarify what happens when ClickHouse isn't running versus when it is. Without ClickHouse, the reachability check fails and tests skip, which is why the generator showed 613 passed with 25 skipped. When ClickHouse is running with the default password, I'm seeing 10 failures in the migration and integration tests that depend on the correct timestamp format.\n\nThe contract technically says \"0 failures\" from `pnpm test`, which is true when ClickHouse isn't running—but that's just skipping tests, not actually verifying them. The real issue is that with ClickHouse running, those integration tests fail due to the production code bugs, so the spirit of the requirement isn't met. So the identity tests are failing for two specific reasons: an auth password mismatch from the environment configuration, and a timestamp format bug in the `insertEvent` function that's actually a pre-existing F4 issue. The sprint contract requires zero test failures, but I need to distinguish between what F32 is responsible for—the test file structure itself—versus environment and upstream production code issues. Let me carefully re-examine the contract requirements and run the tests again without ClickHouse to see what the baseline actually is.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4913,"cache_read_input_tokens":66451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4913},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"623ec6ea-9901-40cd-91c1-46508d69a4ea","uuid":"9314e03b-928b-468b-badb-0a62f8aca4b0"}
