assword. The next sprint should focus on fixing that timestamp format issue in the identity service and ensuring the environment variables are properly configured.\n\nBut I'm realizing the evaluation criteria matters here—the sprint contract explicitly requires tests to run against a live ClickHouse instance, not just pass in a mocked environment. The generator ran the tests without ClickHouse and got 0 failures with 25 skipped, which technically satisfies the \"0 failures\" requirement on paper, but that's not what the sprint actually intended. The F32 spec and the plan both make it clear that these identity integration tests need to run against the real database. So the generator's evaluation was incomplete because they didn't actually run the tests with ClickHouse running.\n\nNow I'm tracing through what happens when the tests do run with ClickHouse—when `CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD=\"\"`, the connection succeeds, the database and tables get created in `beforeAll`, but then the actual test fails because `insertEvent` is generating ISO 8601 timestamps that ClickHouse's DateTime64 type can't parse. That's the real blocker preventing the tests from passing.\n\nThere are also 10 other test failures from unrelated test files that existed before this sprint, but those aren't part of F32's scope—the identity integration tests are what matter here, and they're failing specifically because of that timestamp format issue in the production code.\n\nThis puts the work at a NEEDS_WORK score of 5/10, so I should write up the evaluation and check whether MEMORY.md needs updating.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":541,"cache_read_input_tokens":75460,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":541},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"623ec6ea-9901-40c