{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RwMt6YcEUxAmCSBALnjhRP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No MEMORY.md file. Now let me write the eval file. I need to be precise about what I found.\n\nKey findings:\n1. **All 9 \"file content\" criteria**: PASS (file exists, all 4 scenarios present, uses minipanel_test, beforeAll/afterEach setup correct)\n2. **Test suite → 0 failures**: FAILS\n   - When run without ClickHouse: 0 failures (25 skipped) — this is how generator measured it\n   - When run WITH ClickHouse + default password (\"password\" but server has empty password): 10 failures, 14 skips (identity tests skip due to beforeAll auth failure)\n   - When run WITH ClickHouse + CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD=\"\": 22 failures (identity tests all FAIL with timestamp format error in `insertEvent`)\n3. **Lint**: PASS (exit 0, 31 warnings)\n4. **Typecheck**: PASS (exit 0)\n\nThe core problem is that `insertEvent` in `src/lib/identity.ts:135` generates ISO 8601 timestamps with `T` and `Z` separators, but ClickHouse's DateTime64 type expects a different format in JSONEachRow mode. The `isClickHouseReachable()` function doesn't validate this compatibility.\n\nThe real issue is that `isClickHouseReachable()` only checks TCP connectivity to `/ping`, not authentication. When ClickHouse runs with a different password than expected, the function returns `true` and tests proceed, but then `beforeAll` fails with an auth error, causing Vitest to skip all tests. Against the sprint criteria, this means the execution requirement fails—tests don't actually pass with ClickHouse running, even though the file structure and content meet all other standards.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2949,"cache_read_input_tokens":76001,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2949},"output_tokens":8,"ser